         That is a nerf of dire charm for necromancers.  Before, you could line up 5 mobs, root dot them to 49%, then let your pet finish them off, for a faster rate of experience than using your own mana for that 49%.  You wouldn't suffer an experience penalty for this.  Now, you will suffer an experience penalty for this.  What good is Dire Charm now anyway.  I think they only considered Enchanter DC, where this solution is perfectly acceptable, and didn't realize how it would affect necromancers very negatively.</P><P>They should have just kept the pet experience rules the same for Dire Charmed pets instead of this scaling stuff.</P><P>Anyways, other changes are great!  I'm getting so fed up of this root dot bull, finally I can sit there and heal my pet and let it solo stuff and not get crappy experience!</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
